# TikTok REST API (Express.js)

A simple REST API built with **Express.js** to simulate TikTok backend features.  
It supports CRUD operations for **Users**, **Videos**, and **Comments**, using an in‑memory data store.

---

##  Setup

Install dependencies:

   npm install

# Run the server:
npm run dev
Server runs at: http://localhost:3000

# Endpoints
# Users
GET /api/users → List all users

POST /api/users → Create a new user

GET /api/users/:id → Get user by ID

PUT /api/users/:id → Update user

DELETE /api/users/:id → Delete user

# Videos
GET /api/videos → List all videos

POST /api/videos → Create a new video

GET /api/videos/:id → Get video by ID

PUT /api/videos/:id → Update video

DELETE /api/videos/:id → Delete video

# Comments
GET /api/comments → List all comments

POST /api/comments → Create a new comment

GET /api/comments/:id → Get comment by ID

PUT /api/comments/:id → Update comment

DELETE /api/comments/:id → Delete comment

# Testing
Use curl in VS Code terminal:

curl -X GET http://localhost:3000/api/users
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/users -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"username":"john","email":"john@example.com"}'
Or test with Postman by sending requests to http://localhost:3000.

# Dependencies
express

cors

morgan

body-parser

dotenv

nodemon

# Notes
Data is stored in memory (no database).

Responses are JSON.
Includes basic error handling (400, 404, 409).